# Change Log

## [0.4.7] - 2016-10-11
### Fixed
- Removed broken import

## [0.4.6] - 2016-10-06
### Added
- Set explicit length limit for outgoing SMS
### Removed
- Outgoing call feature
- List numbers feature

## [0.4.4] - 2016-07-26
### Fixed
- Added requests as a requirement for elkme

## [0.4.2] - 2016-07-26
### Changed
- Internal format for the Elks class now takes a `requests` style auth tuple
for username and password instead of a dictionary
- Added deprecation warnings to the help page
- Changed from urllib to requests

### Removed
- Printing HTTP errors, instead raises exceptions
- Removed the `--me` command

## [0.4.1] - 2016-07-25
### Added
- Broke out elks.format_sms_payload from elks.send_sms to support unit testing
- Broke out elks.format_call_payload from elks.make_call to support unit testing
- Support for SMS sending options in the SDK

### Changed
- elks.my_numbers -> elks.list_numbers
- elks.my_user -> elks.list_user
- Fixed internal links to make elkme more appropriate as a SDK

### Removed
- Support for legacy `textme` command
- elks.requires_elements
- Printing within the SDK
- TEMPORARY Debug messages within the SDK
